<br>
He absolutely loves tape... whatever you do, don't leave so much as a centimeter of tape around. He will roll on it, nibble it out of his fur, paw it out of his mouth, nibble it off his paw, paw at it with the other paw... then, eventually when he gets tired of playing &quot;Which Paw Has The Tape&quot; he will stick it to either A) his tail, B) his side, or D) his ear and run around with it for a few hours. When he gets tired of leading his humans on a merry chase (cuz we're concerned as to what that weird looking THING stuck to our baby is) he'll chew it off and eat it.<br>
<br>
We don't even own rolls of tape anymore... mainly because he eats them and we're afraid he'll get sick. We tried sticking double sided tape to a counter once to keep him off... he played the fun game &quot;Look Ma! My Paw Is Stuck!&quot; for a few hours, then he rolled in it till it was a giant mat of fur, then he ate it off the counter.<br>
<br>
Citrus is another beloved friend of his... we can't leave oranges, lemons, or limes on counters... he eats them &lt;sigh&gt;<br>
<br>
Bitter Apple? I think he's convinced it's a signal for &quot;This will be fun to chew on!&quot;<br>
<br>
